place.name: SOUTHBURGH
place.gazetteerText: BURGH-SOUTH, or Southbergh, a parish in Mitford district, Norfolk; on the river Yare, 2½ miles NNW of Hingham, and 3½ WSW of Hardingham r. station. Post Town, Hingham, under Attleborough. Acres, 1,216. Real property, £2,229. Pop., 317. Houses, 62. The property is divided between two. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £249. Patron, B. Gurdon, Esq. The church is fair. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
